tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a slightly low creatinine, which is not clinically concerning and may reflect reduced muscle mass in an elderly patient. No evidence of renal dysfunction, electrolyte imbalance, or abnormal glucose metabolism. Overall, laboratory findings are unremarkable.
